The paper focuses on automating code changes using Neural Machine Translation (NMT) techniques, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The use of NMT also suggests that the paper may fall under the natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with programming languages and their syntax, which could place it under the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach to learning code change patterns, which could also fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
